{"status": "success", "totalResults": 4644, "results": [{"article_id": "02f23f6692d261efd98ba18422b70670", "link": "http://thearabweekly.com/moroccan-entrepreneur-launches-marbella-based-business-network-built-human-connection", "title": "Moroccan entrepreneur launches Marbella-based business network built on human connection", "description": "Moroccan entrepreneur launches Marbella-based business network built on human connection Pitch & Plate aims to respond to what its founder describes as a growing appetite for more meaningful and authentic forms of business engagement. Wednesday 10/06/2026 Moroccan entrepreneur Hanae Morjani. MARBELLA, Spain Moroccan entrepreneur Hanae Morjani has launched Pitch & Plate, a new business and networking concept in Marbella that seeks to place personal stories, cultural exchange and social impact at the centre of professional relationships. Positioned as \u201cThe Human Business Table\u201d, the initiative brings together entrepreneurs, investors, executives, creatives and professionals from different countries in curated gatherings designed to move beyond traditional networking formats. Founded by Morjani, whose professional background spans healthcare, business development, creativity and community building, Pitch & Plate aims to respond to what its founder describes as a growing appetite for more meaningful and authentic forms of business engagement. The concept combines entrepreneurship, gastronomy, culture, entertainment and philanthropy, creating events where participants are encouraged to share the personal journeys behind their professional achievements. Rather than focusing solely on business success, speakers are invited to discuss the challenges, setbacks, turning points and reinventions that shaped their careers, with organisers arguing that such conversations foster deeper trust and more sustainable professional relationships. \u201cPeople are increasingly looking for connections that go beyond titles, transactions and conventional networking,\u201d Morjani said in presenting the initiative. \u201cBusiness today is also about understanding the human story behind each person.\u201d Each edition of Pitch & Plate is hosted in a different venue and incorporates a tailored culinary experience, cultural elements and live entertainment. Organisers describe the format as a meeting point between international business communities, storytelling and lifestyle experiences. A distinctive feature of the initiative is its charitable component, known as The Empty Plate, a symbolic gesture intended to represent individuals who are absent from the table but remain in need of support, visibility or opportunity. According to organisers, the concept is designed to ensure that gatherings generate not only professional opportunities but also social value and community engagement. The project is also expanding beyond live events. Under the umbrella of Pitch & Plate Stories, the brand is developing a podcast and media platform focused on entrepreneurial journeys and personal narratives. Meanwhile, The Pitch Pass, a membership programme currently being rolled out, is expected to provide access to selected events, partner offers, wellness experiences, masterclasses and broader community opportunities. The launch comes as business communities worldwide increasingly explore alternatives to conventional networking models, with growing emphasis on collaboration, authenticity and purpose-driven engagement. For Morjani, Pitch & Plate also reflects the emergence of a new generation of Moroccan entrepreneurs building internationally-oriented ventures from abroad while maintaining strong cultural roots. Born in Marbella but designed with global ambitions, the platform seeks to connect people across industries, nationalities and cultures through a format that combines business opportunities with human connection. As the concept begins to establish itself on Spain\u2019s Costa del Sol, its founder hopes it can evolve into an international community that demonstrates how entrepreneurship, culture and social impact can coexist around the same table.", "content": "ONLY AVAILABLE IN PAID PLANS", "keywords": null, "creator": null, "language": "english", "country": ["kuwait", "qatar", "saudi arabia", "united arab emirates", "libya", "egypt", "tunisia", "syria", "jordan", "bahrain", "lebanon", "iraq", "palestine", "algeria", "morocco"], "category": ["politics", "world"], "datatype": "news", "pubDate": "2026-06-10 13:35:47", "pubDateTZ": "UTC", "fetched_at": "2026-06-10 13:53:40", "image_url": null, "video_url": null, "source_id": "thearabweekly", "source_name": "The Arab Weekly", "source_priority": 118009, "source_url": "https://thearabweekly.com", "source_icon": "https://n.bytvi.com/thearabweekly.png", "sentiment": "ONLY AVAILABLE IN PROFESSIONAL AND CORPORATE PLANS", "sentiment_stats": "ONLY AVAILABLE IN PROFESSIONAL AND CORPORATE PLANS", "ai_tag": "ONLY AVAILABLE IN PROFESSIONAL AND CORPORATE PLANS", "ai_region": "ONLY AVAILABLE IN CORPORATE PLANS", "ai_org": "ONLY AVAILABLE IN CORPORATE PLANS", "ai_summary": "ONLY AVAILABLE IN PAID PLANS", "duplicate": false}, {"article_id": "084c73779d1353bda3968520a19f2919", "link": "https://www.alweeam.com.sa/1278347/2026/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AD%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%81%D8%B7%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%A9-%D9%81%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D9%85%D9%84%D9%83%D8%A9-%D9%88%D8%AC%D9%87%D8%A7%D8%AA-%D8%B3%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%AD%D9%8A/", "title": "\u0627\u0644\u062d\u064a\u0627\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u0641\u0637\u0631\u064a\u0629 \u0641\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0645\u0645\u0644\u0643\u0629.. \u0648\u062c\u0647\u0627\u062a \u0633\u064a\u0627\u062d\u064a\u0629 \u062c\u062f\u064a\u062f\u0629 \u0644\u0627\u0643\u062a\u0634\u0627\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0646\u0648\u0639 \u0627\u0644\u0627\u0654\u062d\u064a\u0627\u064a\u0654\u064a", "description": "\u0627\u0654\u0643\u062f \u0627\u0644\u0631\u064a\u0654\u064a\u0633 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0646\u0641\u064a\u0630\u064a \u0644\u0644